WEBVTT

00:27.486 --> 00:30.023
Oh, that's it, baby.

00:30.197 --> 00:31.733
Yeah.

00:31.907 --> 00:33.568
"Baby"?

00:35.285 --> 00:37.697
I'm over a thousand years old.

00:38.413 --> 00:40.074
Are you not having a good time?

00:40.999 --> 00:44.617
Well, there's just not much thrill left
in feeding on the willing.

00:45.254 --> 00:48.667
Then should I try
pretending not to want it?

00:48.840 --> 00:53.675
Only if you're very, very good at it.

00:56.640 --> 00:59.131
Stop. Get off me.

01:01.019 --> 01:07.140
You sick bloodsucking bastard.

01:15.409 --> 01:16.945
Off you go.

01:20.664 --> 01:22.495
Tell your manager you were magnificent.

01:23.125 --> 01:25.616
l'll back up your story if he calls.

01:31.341 --> 01:35.175
l was beginning to think you weren't
going to accept my invitation, Lorena.

01:35.971 --> 01:40.965
For a vampire, you're a terrible liar.

03:26.623 --> 03:28.614
Tell them to go away.

03:28.792 --> 03:30.748
It could be anyone.

03:34.840 --> 03:38.424
-Who's there?
-lsabel, from the summit.

03:41.805 --> 03:45.844
-And who is this?
-His name is Hugo.

03:46.017 --> 03:47.632
He is mine.

03:54.484 --> 03:57.897
I could see how worried you were
about Sookie infiltrating the Fellowship.

03:58.071 --> 03:59.732
I thought Hugo could help.

03:59.906 --> 04:01.897
And why would you wanna help us?

04:02.075 --> 04:05.488
Because Godric is my sheriff, not yours.

04:05.662 --> 04:10.201
It would be criminal of me to let you take
such a risk without my at least offering.

04:10.375 --> 04:14.288
-And why would you wanna help us?
-Well, I would do anything for Isabel.

04:14.629 --> 04:20.124
Forever, and not just my forever,
your forever, and forever and forever.

04:20.302 --> 04:22.418
It's true, he would.

04:22.596 --> 04:24.006
He loves her.

04:24.181 --> 04:28.140
-You, he loves you very much.
-And | him.

04:29.770 --> 04:33.513
Consider my offer.
If nothing else, with Hugo there...

04:33.690 --> 04:36.022
...Sookie will be less likely
to arouse suspicion.

04:36.193 --> 04:39.310
People of the church,
they have a way of not trusting a woman...

04:39.488 --> 04:41.024
...when she's absent a man.

04:41.198 --> 04:42.278
Bill, l have to say...

04:42.449 --> 04:45.361
...as a woman who's been absent a man
most of her life...

04:45.535 --> 04:47.366
...that could not be more true.

04:51.166 --> 04:53.703
I considered booking you
in the room adjoining theirs...

04:53.877 --> 04:57.461
...but I thought that might be
a bit over the top.

04:57.631 --> 04:59.872
Why am I here, Mr. Northman?

05:00.342 --> 05:02.048
We want the same thing, you and l.

05:04.805 --> 05:08.297
Okay, Bill has something I want...

05:08.475 --> 05:10.386
...and he's in the way.

05:10.560 --> 05:13.723
-His human?
-No, she's something more than human.

05:14.773 --> 05:16.013
What is she?

05:17.108 --> 05:19.315
That I do not know.

05:19.486 --> 05:24.230
But whatever she is, he loves her.

05:25.826 --> 05:28.989
What makes you think I want him back?

05:29.162 --> 05:30.902
That I'd even take him?

05:34.084 --> 05:37.576
Because you didn't come all this way
just to see me.

05:38.588 --> 05:41.876
I haven't seen Bill Compton
in over 70 years.

05:42.050 --> 05:44.917
Surely you can't think l have
any pull over him whatsoever.

05:45.095 --> 05:48.462
I haven't seen my maker
for much longer than that...

05:48.640 --> 05:51.382
...and yet I am still loyal to him.

05:51.726 --> 05:53.102
Fiercely loyal.

05:54.145 --> 05:56.227
Shame I didn't turn you.

05:58.275 --> 05:59.936
Then again...

06:01.570 --> 06:03.606
...you're not really my type.

06:51.453 --> 06:53.364
Enjoying the entertainment?

06:53.538 --> 06:55.620
Oh, yes. Very much.

06:55.790 --> 06:58.497
Yes, he's wonderful. Just wonderful.

07:02.839 --> 07:05.171
He is quite wonderful.

07:06.593 --> 07:10.586
I love your necklace. lt's extraordinary.

07:10.764 --> 07:14.598
Oh, thank you. I love it too.
It was a gift from Sidney.

07:14.768 --> 07:16.884
Yeah, it cost me a pretty penny...

07:17.062 --> 07:19.678
...but got me out of
a whopper of a fight, huh?

07:19.856 --> 07:21.517
Right, doll?

07:22.525 --> 07:26.985
Hey, where'd you say you two
were all from again? Was it Miss...?

07:27.155 --> 07:32.445
Olivier. Faviana Olivier.
And we are from Europe. France.

07:32.619 --> 07:36.032
I'm hoping to hop over the pond
sometime soon, take this one with me.

07:36.414 --> 07:38.575
I've always wanted to see Europe.

07:38.750 --> 07:43.289
You would like it.
And it would certainly like you.

07:45.340 --> 07:49.504
You seem European already.

07:50.553 --> 07:55.047
Most Americans these days
are so puritanical.

07:56.893 --> 07:57.973
Fuck prohibition.

07:58.144 --> 07:59.429
-Sidney.
-Yes.

07:59.604 --> 08:04.724
-He's so crass.
-But he's right. Fuck prohibition.

08:14.285 --> 08:18.995
If you'd like,
after your other guests leave...

08:19.165 --> 08:22.282
...Guillaume and I could stay
and we could all...

08:22.460 --> 08:26.578
...fuck prohibition somewhat further.

08:29.426 --> 08:32.338
-Absolutely.
-Okay.

08:43.982 --> 08:46.348
-Wonderful.
-This gentleman is wonderful.

08:48.069 --> 08:49.104
Smashing.

09:18.558 --> 09:20.514
lam Guillaume.

09:39.496 --> 09:41.077
Hey.

09:41.748 --> 09:43.659
What happened here?

09:45.043 --> 09:48.035
Oh, baby, if you don't wanna tell me....

09:48.546 --> 09:50.286
It's all right.

09:50.673 --> 09:55.542
It's just when I take my clothes off,
it's all anybody ever sees.

09:56.387 --> 10:00.676
The answer is |--
I don't know what happened.

10:01.351 --> 10:04.093
-You mean you don't remember?
-Oh, I remember.

10:04.270 --> 10:06.682
Heck, I'll never forget it.

10:06.856 --> 10:11.771
| just never got a look at who
or what it was that jumped me.

10:12.737 --> 10:15.274
Jesus. Where were you?

10:15.448 --> 10:18.485
In the woods, running.

10:18.660 --> 10:23.575
And then whatever it was, it was on me.

10:23.748 --> 10:24.863
lt slashed me.

10:25.458 --> 10:28.245
And then I was sick, real sick, for weeks.

10:28.419 --> 10:32.662
Doctors couldn't figure out what it was.

10:33.258 --> 10:38.423
They told me l was lucky to be alive,
and I should count my blessings.

10:39.139 --> 10:42.472
And I still do, every single day of my life.

10:43.518 --> 10:49.309
You are the most amazing person...

10:49.482 --> 10:50.892
...l've ever met.

10:52.485 --> 10:55.852
You're just saying that because
I'm the first honest sex you've ever had.

10:56.030 --> 10:58.237
No, that's not true.

11:00.743 --> 11:04.452
Have you told anybody else
what you are?

11:06.166 --> 11:09.078
Yeah. My--

11:09.252 --> 11:12.585
My friend Sookie. She knows.

11:13.339 --> 11:16.957
And have you slept with her?

11:18.094 --> 11:19.595
No.

11:19.762 --> 11:22.754
Well, I rest my case.

11:27.937 --> 11:31.850
Seriously though, Sam,
you shouldn't be ashamed of what you are.

11:32.025 --> 11:33.765
I'm not ashamed.

11:33.943 --> 11:36.685
-| just don't go around advertising it.
-Well, neither do |.

11:36.863 --> 11:40.151
But the people that I know,
the people that I love...

11:40.325 --> 11:42.281
...I don't keep it a secret from them.

11:44.996 --> 11:47.078
How come you do?

11:48.458 --> 11:51.325
I guess it's because
it's dangerous out there.

11:52.587 --> 11:54.373
It's like, why take the risk?

11:56.966 --> 12:00.629
Because not taking a risk is riskier.

12:02.805 --> 12:04.636
That's just wordplay.

12:06.226 --> 12:09.138
No. No, it's not.

12:10.063 --> 12:14.602
The way I look at it, if you're gonna take the
danger out of getting to know someone...

12:14.776 --> 12:16.812
...might as well
not bother with them at all.

12:17.570 --> 12:21.154
You've gotta share this life with people.

12:22.867 --> 12:25.404
It's what we were put on
this big old round ball to do.

12:25.912 --> 12:28.949
And people, they need to know you.

12:32.919 --> 12:36.082
You're just too damn special
for them not to.

12:37.423 --> 12:39.334
Where the fuck did you come from?

12:51.437 --> 12:54.850
I'm looking for a pump
for an A.O. Smith water heater.

12:55.024 --> 12:58.266
-Can you hold on?
-Yeah, I'll hold.

12:58.444 --> 12:59.479
Shit.

12:59.654 --> 13:02.270
Want me to take a look
and you can hold the line?

13:02.448 --> 13:06.487
That was some spiteful shit, what you said.
I got this, okay? I'm the man of the house.

13:07.537 --> 13:09.323
-No offense, Karl.
-None taken.

13:10.999 --> 13:12.034
How's your coffee?

13:13.084 --> 13:16.451
Colder than that ridiculous excuse
for a shower.

13:16.629 --> 13:18.039
I don't know what to tell you.

13:18.214 --> 13:21.126
| wish I had a fancier crib
for you to squat in, but I don't.

13:22.635 --> 13:27.720
Tara, you may not know this about me,
but without a hot shower in the morning...

13:27.890 --> 13:30.222
...l have no tolerance for sarcasm.

13:30.393 --> 13:32.054
-Sorry.
-You still there?

13:32.228 --> 13:33.468
Yeah. Yeah, I'm here.

13:33.646 --> 13:34.886
-Yeah, we got one.
-You do?

13:35.064 --> 13:38.227
-Yep.
-Great. We'll be there as soon as we can.

13:38.401 --> 13:40.642
Hardware shop in Ferriday's
got the part we need.

13:40.820 --> 13:43.562
Ferriday is over two hours away.

13:43.740 --> 13:45.355
It's an old water heater, Maryann.

13:45.533 --> 13:47.865
I called everyone I could
within a 150-mile radius.

13:48.036 --> 13:50.903
This guy's the only one
who's got a pump that'll fit it.

13:51.080 --> 13:53.241
So do you want somebody
to go get it or not?

13:55.918 --> 13:57.909
Drive like the wind.

13:58.921 --> 14:02.129
-Maybe Eggs ought to come--
-I want him working on the water heater...

14:02.300 --> 14:06.669
...in case he can jury-rig something
so I can take some semblance of a shower.

14:07.096 --> 14:09.508
Maryann, lthink
you're overestimating your plumber.

14:10.183 --> 14:14.552
Besides, if I have to drive a car and look at
a map at the same time, I'll crash your Jag.

14:14.729 --> 14:16.344
I know I Will.

14:21.110 --> 14:23.522
You can go. Go, go, go.

14:23.696 --> 14:25.277
Cool.

14:32.663 --> 14:34.949
Where you been, Stackhouse?
We're 10 minutes late.

14:35.124 --> 14:37.240
Didn't they say
what they wanted to see us for?

14:37.418 --> 14:41.127
All they said was to grab you and
get our butts down to the sanctuary lawn.

14:41.297 --> 14:45.006
-Why, you think it's something bad?
-It can't be good.

14:47.136 --> 14:48.592
Good morning.

14:53.434 --> 14:55.595
-Think you can handle it?
-Yeah.

14:55.770 --> 14:57.431
-Oh, yeah.
-|t's just a--

14:57.605 --> 14:59.937
Well, it's a platform
with a cross on top of it.

15:00.108 --> 15:03.316
-Seems pretty straightfon/vard.
-Good. Good, good.

15:03.861 --> 15:07.649
Look, I'm sorry, but the rest of the group,
they're back at camp training, right?

15:07.824 --> 15:09.485
Shouldn't we be with them?

15:11.327 --> 15:13.818
I mean, we ain't being punished
for something, are we?

15:14.247 --> 15:18.991
Jason Stackhouse, of all the things.
Now, what would we be punishing you for?

15:23.506 --> 15:25.792
Nothing. Nothing at all.

15:25.967 --> 15:27.923
Well, then how about you stop sulking...

15:28.094 --> 15:31.086
...and try to be a little thankful
for the job you've been given?

15:34.684 --> 15:35.924
Oh, my golly.

15:36.102 --> 15:38.935
You know,
I didn't even think of the parallels.

15:40.857 --> 15:43.690
-Should we tell them?
-I don't think that's such a good idea.

15:43.860 --> 15:46.522
Honey, they're the best of the best.
They deserve to know.

15:46.696 --> 15:48.357
Now, can you boys keep a secret?

15:48.614 --> 15:50.821
-I hope so.
-|'|| take it to the grave.

15:50.992 --> 15:55.281
This platform we're having you build,
it's for a ceremony.

15:55.455 --> 15:58.663
Have either of you ever heard
the expression "meet the sun"?

16:00.042 --> 16:01.703
You for real?

16:01.878 --> 16:04.915
-Steve--
-Sarah, I'm talking.

16:05.423 --> 16:08.005
Luke, you wanna do the honors?

16:10.136 --> 16:14.300
Well, if it's what I read about, meeting
the sun's when you take a vampire...

16:14.474 --> 16:16.681
...and chain him to the cross
just before dawn.

16:17.226 --> 16:20.718
When the sun comes up, the congregation
gets to watch from the bleachers...

16:20.897 --> 16:24.355
...as a vampire ignites,
sent to his fiery grave once and for all.

16:26.068 --> 16:29.731
-Jesus Christ.
-Well, yes, him, but the sun too.

16:31.407 --> 16:33.068
Get to work, boys.

16:34.035 --> 16:36.572
-You should probably wear this.
-Oh, Hugo.

16:36.746 --> 16:39.704
Yes. Yes, a thousand times, yes.

16:39.874 --> 16:43.537
And also, just so that they believe
that we're a couple about to get married...

16:43.711 --> 16:46.578
...it'd probably be best if you let me
do most of the talking.

16:46.756 --> 16:50.089
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
I'll just shut up and look pretty.

16:50.343 --> 16:52.584
-That's not what I meant.
-Yes, it was.

16:52.762 --> 16:55.128
It's okay.
It'll be easier to listen in on others...

16:55.306 --> 16:58.093
...if I don't have to worry
about carrying on a conversation.

16:58.267 --> 17:00.883
Good, good.
But if they do ask you any questions...

17:01.062 --> 17:04.395
...are you sure you're gonna be able
to say the things about vampires...

17:04.565 --> 17:06.647
-...that they're gonna wanna hear?
-Hugo...

17:06.817 --> 17:09.399
...l don'tjust hear the things
that hateful people say.

17:09.570 --> 17:11.435
I hear the things that are so hateful...

17:11.614 --> 17:14.572
...that hateful people
don't even wanna say them out loud.

17:14.742 --> 17:15.902
Don't you worry about me.

17:16.077 --> 17:18.784
I've got plenty of material to work with.
I'll be fine.

17:18.955 --> 17:20.445
Good.

17:20.790 --> 17:24.783
It's funny, I don't even know you really,
but you're the only other person...

17:24.961 --> 17:26.792
...l've ever met who's dated a vampire--

17:26.963 --> 17:28.499
What do you wanna know?

17:30.091 --> 17:31.126
Everything.

17:32.176 --> 17:35.634
Like do you and Isabel ever fight?

17:35.805 --> 17:36.965
Oh, we fight like crazy.

17:37.848 --> 17:40.260
But I've been with women
I didn't fight with before.

17:40.434 --> 17:43.301
With every one of them,
the only reason that we never fought...

17:43.479 --> 17:46.186
...was because
I didn't care enough to bother.

17:46.357 --> 17:49.315
Oh, Hugo, that is messed up.

17:49.860 --> 17:52.567
Maybe. But it's also true.

17:52.738 --> 17:58.199
It's funny, but whenever Bill and me fight,
even as I'm screaming and I'm so mad...

17:58.369 --> 18:02.988
...I don't think I'm ever gonna stop,
somehow, in the middle of all that...

18:03.165 --> 18:05.872
...I know we're both fighting
for our relationship.

18:06.043 --> 18:07.624
For each other.

18:07.795 --> 18:11.162
-We're fighting to stay together.
-Do you--?

18:12.091 --> 18:15.003
-Never mind.
-What?

18:15.970 --> 18:19.838
Lately, the thing Isabel and I
have been fighting about the most...

18:20.224 --> 18:23.432
...is whenever I bring up the subject
of her turning me...

18:23.603 --> 18:25.844
...she just shuts down.
She won't even discuss it.

18:26.606 --> 18:31.100
Is that a thing that people actually do?
Because it never even occurred to me.

18:31.277 --> 18:34.189
How could it not?
I mean, right now it's all well and good...

18:34.363 --> 18:36.854
...but in 50 years,
when they're still what they are...

18:37.033 --> 18:38.944
...but we're in our 703 and 80s...

18:39.118 --> 18:41.825
...and we're hunched over and frail
and using walkers?

18:42.204 --> 18:44.820
Come on. How could they still love us?

18:50.463 --> 18:52.078
We should go.

18:54.050 --> 18:56.917
Listen, I'm so sorry.
I shouldn't have told you that. I--

18:57.094 --> 19:02.214
It's okay, Hugo, really.
Besides, now if I die today, who cares?

19:02.391 --> 19:06.384
I'll never have to feel old
and unloved and unwanted.

19:07.647 --> 19:09.262
Right.

19:14.737 --> 19:21.734
"Bitches, don't you know that sarcasm
and cold water do not mix?"

19:24.372 --> 19:25.987
Oh, shit.

19:26.165 --> 19:30.033
All right, so the next thing you wanna do
is hop on the 165 South.

19:30.211 --> 19:33.578
Excellent.
You're a hell of a navigator, you know?

19:47.937 --> 19:49.268
Eggs?

19:49.438 --> 19:52.601
Okay, there's gonna be a diner
that's built out of an old red barn...

19:52.775 --> 19:54.515
...coming up around the bend.

19:54.694 --> 19:57.231
-You been here before?
-No, never.

19:59.365 --> 20:02.653
-Now, why the fuck did I know that?
-All right, you're freaking me out.

20:02.827 --> 20:05.614
-You better not be fucking with me.
-No, no. Turn right here.

20:05.788 --> 20:07.904
-Eggs, tell me what's going on.
-I don't know.

20:08.082 --> 20:10.573
-Please, just turn right here. Come on.
-Shit.

20:30.896 --> 20:32.761
Eggs.

20:45.327 --> 20:47.659
Where you going, Eggs?

20:54.503 --> 20:57.415
You still up for doing something
after work tonight?

20:57.590 --> 20:59.455
Yeah. Sure.

20:59.633 --> 21:05.594
Good, because ljust got off the phone,
and I've got a surprise lined up for you.

21:07.183 --> 21:09.549
I don't like surprises, Arlene.

21:09.727 --> 21:11.183
Well, that's too bad...

21:11.353 --> 21:17.019
...because I just happen to be
an extremely mysterious woman.

21:20.362 --> 21:21.772
Can I get y'all anything else?

21:21.947 --> 21:24.279
How about that iced tea
I ordered five minutes ago?

21:24.450 --> 21:27.237
Oh, my gosh, I am so sorry.
I'll be right back with that.

21:27.411 --> 21:29.743
And some Worcestershire.

21:31.707 --> 21:33.698
-Any chance I'll get it?
-Zero.

21:33.876 --> 21:37.243
-She's about the worst I've ever seen.
-Well, maybe it's for the best.

21:37.421 --> 21:40.003
Seems like lately
if you're too good a waitress...

21:40.174 --> 21:42.256
...someone's gonna come along
and kill you.

21:42.426 --> 21:44.542
You are so bad, Maxine.

21:47.640 --> 21:49.722
Hey there, Sam. Lafayette here?

21:49.892 --> 21:51.723
In the kitchen.

21:55.272 --> 21:58.389
I've been noticing some strange things
about you lately.

21:59.193 --> 22:00.399
Like?

22:00.569 --> 22:03.356
Like the fact that you just up and vanish
for over two weeks.

22:03.531 --> 22:07.649
Like the fact that now that you are back,
you seem to have lost some of your pizzazz.

22:09.578 --> 22:11.830
-My pizzazz?
-That's right.

22:13.290 --> 22:17.533
Now, in case you didn't hear, Lafayette,
a woman's dead.

22:17.711 --> 22:21.249
A woman thatjust so happened to have
ripped off your cousin and your auntie.

22:21.882 --> 22:25.716
So for the record,
where were you all that time?

22:27.263 --> 22:28.924
I was on a cruise.

22:29.431 --> 22:31.683
A cruise, huh? What kind of cruise?

22:31.851 --> 22:33.091
A gay one.

22:34.228 --> 22:36.469
Why don't you tell me
what you're accusing me of?

22:36.647 --> 22:38.433
You weren't on any damn gay cruise.

22:39.275 --> 22:42.688
Because if you were, you would have
come back with more pizzazz, not less.

22:43.320 --> 22:47.108
So how about you and I go down
to the station and I lock you up?

22:47.283 --> 22:50.867
Leave you in a cell to rot
until you confess.

22:51.245 --> 22:52.951
Or you can just tell me now.

22:54.832 --> 22:57.118
Because I already know
what you were doing.

22:57.293 --> 22:59.830
You were hiding out. Lying in wait.

23:00.004 --> 23:03.212
You killed that woman
and cut her heart out.

23:03.799 --> 23:05.630
Now, tell me I'm not right.

23:06.051 --> 23:09.964
-Leave him alone, 002.
-Terry, you need to shut up.

23:10.139 --> 23:14.098
And you need to get up.
Think I will take you down to the station.

23:14.268 --> 23:16.680
I said get the fuck up.

23:17.438 --> 23:19.679
What the hell, Andy?
Back when we were kids...

23:19.857 --> 23:23.520
...and we used to play Cops and Robbers
in Me-maw and Pa-po's backyard...

23:23.694 --> 23:26.811
...you always used to make your arrests
