I feel like that kid in E. T.

43:17.386 --> 43:20.378
Except instead of following Reese's Pieces,
we following clothes.

43:20.556 --> 43:24.344
I ain't never seen E. T., but Reese's Pieces
sound real good right now.

43:24.519 --> 43:26.305
Don't they though?

45:15.296 --> 45:18.288
-Who is it?
-It's-- It's Hoyt.

45:19.800 --> 45:21.256
Hoyt?

45:21.427 --> 45:25.136
Come on, open up.
I know you must be mad at me.

45:25.306 --> 45:28.013
I'm so sorry.
My mama canceled my cell service...

45:28.184 --> 45:30.391
...and I had no way
to get in touch with you.

45:30.561 --> 45:33.143
I got here as fast as I could.

45:36.776 --> 45:38.767
I'm so sorry, Jessica.

45:39.195 --> 45:42.483
I can't believe it.
You came all this way?

45:43.658 --> 45:45.239
You're not mad at me?

45:46.369 --> 45:48.906
No. I'm so happy I could cry...

45:49.080 --> 45:51.822
...but I don't want to,
because it's really gross when I do.

45:54.001 --> 45:57.334
I'm sorry about the flowers too.
I got them in Bon Temps before I left.

45:57.505 --> 46:00.247
-It was just really hot in my car.
-No, they're beautiful.

46:17.525 --> 46:19.015
Hello.

46:20.695 --> 46:23.778
Steve? Sarah?

46:25.366 --> 46:26.947
Anyone?

46:27.868 --> 46:31.452
I'm up here. Up here on the balcony.

46:33.249 --> 46:36.787
Hey. I just wanted to tell you
that Luke and me...

46:36.961 --> 46:39.873
...we're done with the platform.

46:40.047 --> 46:41.378
Great.

46:42.383 --> 46:44.089
Thank you.

46:46.345 --> 46:48.381
Hey, are you crying?

46:49.307 --> 46:50.888
No.

46:58.232 --> 47:00.848
I'm sorry.
You're not supposed to see me like this.

47:01.319 --> 47:03.184
No, it's okay. Really.

47:04.989 --> 47:08.607
-What's the matter?
-|t's Steve.

47:09.952 --> 47:12.068
He's not the man I thought he was.

47:13.539 --> 47:16.747
Sarah, your husband is a great man.

47:17.918 --> 47:21.752
And I feel bad
about what we did last night too.

47:22.423 --> 47:25.256
But we can't try to make it
easier on ourselves by--

47:25.426 --> 47:26.757
By blaming the victim.

47:27.636 --> 47:29.251
Jason”.

47:29.889 --> 47:32.596
...you and Luke and all the others...

47:33.351 --> 47:35.387
...you're not being trained to defend us.

47:37.438 --> 47:41.397
He wants to use you to start a war.

47:41.650 --> 47:44.266
Does that sound like a great man to you?

47:45.988 --> 47:48.775
-What?
-Well, he's not one.

47:49.950 --> 47:52.282
And I thought he was...

47:53.496 --> 47:56.909
...but lately I've been seeing
a side of him I never did before.

47:58.292 --> 48:02.501
He's vicious and he's cruel,
and he uses the C-word.

48:04.548 --> 48:06.925
And he lies to me, Jason.

48:07.093 --> 48:11.427
Our marriage has always been a partnership,
but now he's shutting me out.

48:13.182 --> 48:15.639
Come on, now. Here.

48:16.102 --> 48:17.888
Don't cry.

48:20.606 --> 48:22.892
There. All gone.

48:31.700 --> 48:35.318
-I should go.
-When I was a little girl...

48:36.288 --> 48:39.121
...I realized that I had a calling.

48:40.000 --> 48:44.164
That I was put here on this earth to be
that great woman behind her great man.

48:44.839 --> 48:48.627
And when Steve came into my life,
I thought he was that man.

48:50.511 --> 48:52.672
But now I see it...

48:53.222 --> 48:55.213
...clear as day.

48:56.559 --> 48:58.766
I'm supposed to be with you.

49:00.312 --> 49:01.973
Hey, hey, whoa, whoa, whoa.

49:03.816 --> 49:05.932
We can't. It's wrong.

49:08.362 --> 49:10.523
-You're married.
-Not in my heart.

49:12.199 --> 49:13.530
Not anymore.

49:14.452 --> 49:20.618
And how can this be wrong
if it's what God's commanding me to do?

49:23.919 --> 49:27.787
Think God really wants this?

49:29.049 --> 49:30.710
Yes.

49:34.847 --> 49:40.058
-You talk to him?
-Every single day of my life.

49:41.729 --> 49:44.141
And he wants this, Jason.

49:44.315 --> 49:48.308
Oh, God, I promise.

49:57.161 --> 49:58.742
Okay.

50:19.892 --> 50:22.725
-Where are you taking me?
-Don't be such a nervous nelly.

50:22.895 --> 50:24.931
It's a surprise.

50:33.447 --> 50:36.029
What? You don't like drums?

50:36.200 --> 50:41.115
No. It'sjust that in my experience,
no good can come from drum music.

50:41.914 --> 50:44.656
Follow it and all it ever leads you to
is hippies and cults.

50:45.292 --> 50:46.372
Not this time.

50:50.130 --> 50:51.791
Hey!

50:51.966 --> 50:54.582
-Daphne?
-Sorry, Sam.

50:55.636 --> 50:56.967
What the hell's going on?

51:20.786 --> 51:22.401
What the fuck is this?

51:23.080 --> 51:24.661
It's the end of the road.

51:59.992 --> 52:04.235
No! No!
